						<div class="postbody">From another post on this forum someone linked to a complete set of very nicely computer drawn schematics for the Famicom on this site : <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www43.tok2.com/home/cmpslv/Famic/Famic.htm">http://www43.tok2.com/home/cmpslv/Famic/Famic.htm</a><!-- m --><br /><br />There are controller schematics that show how the microphone is wired.  All it doesn't do is to give identifying information for the microphone itself.  <br /><br />I could see adding a microphone input to the top loader as well because it has two discrete 40H368s, which give twelve total gates to use.  It would be easy enough to determine whether 4016 D2 is already connected to the appropriate chip.  If not, one wire would be all it would take to connect the gate and then it would be simple to follow the diagram.</div>

					
